o formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_006, mol_002, mol_001 -> mol_007 (Hydrothermal carbon fixation from formate to acetate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005, mol_008 (Magnetite-catalyzed Fischer-Tropsch-type generation of formaldehyde and acetaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_009 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from carbon dioxide and hydrogen) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_001, mol_003 -> mol_004 (TiO2-assisted photochemical formation of hydrogen cyanide from simple carbon and nitrogen feedstocks) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_005 -> mol_008 (Borate-stabilized formose entry from formaldehyde to acetaldehyde-accessible carbonyl pool) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_009 -> mol_008, mol_001 (Pyruvate decarboxylation to acetaldehyde) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_008: mol_008, mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_012 (Surface Strecker synthesis of valine aminonitrile from acetaldehyde, hydrogen cyanide, and ammonia) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_004, mol_003 -> mol_010, mol_015 (Alternative surface nitrile buildup from hydrogen cyanide to aminated nitrile precursor pool) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_009, mol_008 -> mol_013 (Prebiotic carbon-carbon elaboration from pyruvate and acetaldehyde to alpha-ketoisovalerate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_012 -> mol_014 (Hydrolysis of valine aminonitrile to valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_013, mol_003 -> mol_014 (Reductive amination or transamination of alpha-ketoisovalerate to valine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal pyruvate to branched keto acid to valine (4 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal pyruvate to aldehyde Strecker route (4 steps)\n  - P3: Formate-acetate-pyruvate convergence route (6 steps)\n  - P4: Fischer-Tropsch aldehyde to Strecker valine (4 steps)\n  - P5: Formaldehyde surface carbonyl elaboration to Strecker valine (5 steps)\n  - P6: Pyruvate plus photochemical cyanide dual-input route (5 steps)\n  - P7: Direct aldehyde to branched keto acid route (4