nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Valine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets valine through two chemically distinct but connected prebiotic routes that avoid the incorrect direct Strecker derivation from acetaldehyde. The dominant route builds the correct branched carbon skeleton first as 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoic acid (alpha-ketoisovalerate) via pyruvate-centered C-C bond formation and carbonyl rearrangement, then converts that keto acid to valine by reductive amination/transamination in biochemical settings. A secondary convergent route forms 2-amino-3-methylbutanenitrile (valine aminonitrile) from the correct aldehyde precursor 2-methylpropanal under surface Strecker conditions, followed by hydrolysis to valine. Hydrothermal chemistry supplies CO2 reduction products, pyruvate, acetate, and simple aldehydes; surface chemistry supplies HCN, formaldehyde-derived sugars/carbonyls, branched aldehydes, and aminonitriles; biochemical settings complete amino acid assembly and interconvert hubs. The hub molecules are HCN, pyruvate, 2-methylpropanal, 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoic acid, and valine aminonitrile, providing dense connectivity and multiple convergent paths.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: CHN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H8O (isobutyraldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H7NO2 (alpha-ketoisovaleric acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C5H10N2 (valine aminonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H11NO2 (valine) [target]\n  - mol_015: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Greigite-catalyzed reduction of CO2 to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_006 (Further hydrothermal carbon fixation from formate/CO2 to acetate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_005, mol_006, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_007 (Hydrothermal pyruvate synthesis from reduced carbon pool) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_007, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Hydrothermal reductive amination of pyruvate to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_005: mol_001, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_004 (TiO2-assisted photochemical generation of HCN from reduced C/N feedstocks) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_008 (Surface reduction of C1 carbon to formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_008 -> mol_009 (Borate-stabilized formose entry to glycolaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_008: mol_009, mol_008 -> mol_010 (Aldol extension from glycolaldehyde to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_007, mol_010 -> mol_011 (Surface carbonyl rearrangement to branched aldehyde 2-methylpropanal) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_011, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_013 (Branched Strecker synthesis of valine aminonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_011: mol_013 -> mol_014 (Hydrolysis of valine aminonitrile to valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_012: mol_007, mol_015 -> mol_012, mol_014 (Biochemical branched-chain keto acid synthesis and amination to valine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal keto-acid route to valine (5 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal-to-surface Strecker route (7 steps)\n  - P3: Formate-mediated surface carbonyl pool to valine (7 steps)\n  - P4: HCN-first branched aminonitrile route (4 steps)\n  - P5: Sugar-assisted pyruvate branching route (8 steps)\n  - P6: Acetate-supported pyruvate-to-ketoisovalerate route (4 steps)\n  - P7: Alanine-assisted transamination route (5 steps)\n  - P8: Dual-hub convergence 