{"timestamp": "2026-03-19T15:26:56.144339", "agent_name": "CriticAgent", "method_name": "evaluate_network", "step": null, "attempt": null, "system_message": "You are evaluating a COMPLETE SYNTHESIS NETWORK, not individual reactions.\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\n### 1. Network Topology (0.0-1.0)\n- Are there sufficient molecule and reaction nodes?\n- Are hub molecules properly connected (degree \u2265 3)?\n- Are there convergent pathways?\n- Is the network connected (no isolated subgraphs)?\n\n### 2. Chemical Feasibility (0.0-1.0)\n- Is each reaction chemically sound?\n- Are the conditions appropriate for each environment?\n- Are the mechanisms plausible?\n\n### 3. Environmental Interconnection (0.0-1.0)\n- Does the network show Hydrothermal \u2194 Surface \u2192 Biochemical flow?\n- Are environmental transitions justified (e.g., hydrothermal products feeding surface reactions)?\n- Are conditions realistic for each stage?\n- Do Hydrothermal and Surface reactions specify mineral agents?\n\n### 4. Pathway Coherence (0.0-1.0)\n- Do pathways form valid routes to the target?\n- Are key intermediates properly identified?\n- Is the overall strategy sound?\n\n### 5. Target Achievement (0.0-1.0)\n- Does the network actually produce the target molecule?\n- Are the final steps chemically valid?\n\n### 6. Literature Alignment (0.0-1.0) - When research findings are provided\n- Does the network align with known prebiotic synthesis routes from literature?\n- Are reactions supported by experimental evidence from cited studies?\n- Are literature citations present in reaction reasoning?\n- Does the network address known challenges identified in the research?\n\n## Scoring Guidelines\n- 0.9-1.0: Excellent network, well-connected, chemically sound\n- 0.8-0.9: Good network with minor issues\n- 0.7-0.8: Acceptable but with notable concerns\n- 0.5-0.7: Significant problems with topology or chemistry\n- 0.0-0.5: Major issues, network is not viable\n\nA network is APPROVED if overall_confidence >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Valine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets valine through two chemically distinct but interconnected prebiotic routes built around better-specified branched-carbon intermediates than prior failed attempts. Hydrothermal iron-sulfur chemistry generates reduced C1-C3 feedstocks (formate, acetate, pyruvate) and NH3. Surface chemistry supplies HCN and carbonyl diversification, including a Strecker branch from the correct branched aldehyde 2-methylpropanal to valine aminonitrile, followed by hydrolysis to valine. In parallel, a biochemical/prebiotic route proceeds from pyruvate to acetolactate to 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate (alpha-ketoisovalerate), then transamination/reductive amination to valine. Convergence is organized around five hub molecules: HCN, pyruvate, acetaldehyde, 2-methylpropanal, and 3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate. Ten pathways are enumerated by combining convergent upstream routes with the two downstream valine-forming branches while maintaining a single connected bipartite graph spanning Hydrothermal \u2194 Surface \u2192 Biochemical environments.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formic acid/formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetic acid/acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: C3H4O3 (pyruvic acid/pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O (acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C6H10O5 (acetolactic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C5H8O3 (alpha-ketoisovaleric acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H8O (isobutyraldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C5H10N2 (valine aminonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C5H11NO2 (valine) [target]\n  - mol_014: CO (carbon monoxide) [starting]\n  - mol_015: H2O (water) [starting]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_001, mol_002, mol_014 -> mol_006 (Hydrothermal carbon fixation to acetate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002, mol_006 -> mol_007 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from reduced carbon feedstocks) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_007 -> mol_008, mol_001 (Thermal decarboxylation of pyruvate to acetaldehyde) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_005: mol_002, mol_003, mol_014 -> mol_004, mol_015 (Surface photochemical generation of HCN from reduced C/N feedstocks) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_014, mol_003 -> mol_004, mol_015 (Alternative hydrothermal nitrile generation feeding the HCN pool) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_007: mol_007, mol_008 -> mol_009 (Prebiotic aldol-type condensation from pyruvate and acetaldehyde to acetolactate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_008: mol_009 -> mol_010 (Conversion of acetolactate to alpha-ketoisovalerate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_009: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_013 (Transamination/reductive amination of alpha-ketoisovalerate to valine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_010: mol_010, mol_002 -> mol_011, mol_001 (Reduction of alpha-ketoisovalerate to 2-methylpropanal) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_011, mol_003, mol_004 -> mol_012 (Surface Strecker synthesis of valine aminonitrile from 2-methylpropanal) [Surface]\n  - rxn_012: mol_012, mol_015 -> mol_013 (Hydrolysis of valine aminonitrile to valine) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal keto-acid route from acetate-derived pyruvate (6 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal keto-acid route from formate-supported pyruvate (6 steps)\n  - P3: Direct pyruvate-start keto-acid route (5 steps)\n  - P4: Surface-HCN Strecker route with surface-origin HCN (8 steps)\n  - P5: Surface-HCN Strecker route with hydrothermal nitrile support (8 steps)\n  - P6: Acetate-led Strecker route (8 steps)\n  - P7: Formate-assisted Strecker route (8 steps)\n  - P8: HCN-first convergent route via hydrothermal pyruvate (8 steps)\n  - P9: Dual-HCN reservoir route (9 steps)\n  - P10: Network-spanning full environmental route (10 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_004, mol_007, mol_008, mol_010, mol_011\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.85,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.78,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_007\": 0.48,\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.44,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.58\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.60,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.75,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.78,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.72,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.66,\n      \"feedback\": \"This hydrothermal-to-biochemical keto-acid route is topologically coherent and reaches valine, but the key biochemical transformations are underjustified. Hydrothermal formate and acetate generation are plausible, whereas pyruvate synthesis from CO2/H2/a